                <head>No. 1462<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Telegram 386 from Jidda, March 10, reported on King <persName corresp="#p_SIAA1"
                        >Saud</persName>’s first major speech from the throne inaugurating the
                    Council of Ministers in Riyadh on March 7. He announced, among other things,
                    that the Ministry of Finance would become a ministry in the true meaning of the
                    word. It would control expenditures within an authorized budget, parts of which
                    would be submitted to the Council of Ministers. Telegram 395 from Jidda, March
                    17, reported that a Financial Committee of the Council had been established to
                    make a preliminary study of various budgets. The King was reported to be
                    actively participating in the Council proceedings. Documentation is in
                    Department of State file 786A.00.</p>
            </div>
